  Locus:
    Page: 271
    Verse: 20
Tags:
  - Immortality/Eternity
---
In our quiet moments, when we are not relating to traditional
thinking patterns, we are certain of our own immortality and of the promise
life holds for us. We know that we did not begin at conception, and that we
will not end when the body is no longer able to serve our needs.
